{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Act|11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","chapter":11,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":1,"text":"The apostles and the brothers and sisters who were throughout Judea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":2,"text":"When Peter went up to Jerusalem, the circumcision party criticized him,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":3,"text":"saying, “You went to uncircumcised men and ate with them.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":4,"text":"Peter began to explain to them step by step,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":5,"text":"“I was in the town of Joppa praying, and I saw, in a trance, an object that resembled a large sheet coming down, being lowered by its four corners from heaven, and it came to me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":6,"text":"When I looked closely and considered it, I saw the four-footed animals of the earth, the wild beasts, the reptiles, and the birds of the sky.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":7,"text":"I also heard a voice telling me, ‘Get up, Peter; kill and eat.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":8,"text":"“ ‘No, Lord!’ I said. ‘For nothing impure or ritually unclean has ever entered my mouth.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":9,"text":"But a voice answered from heaven a second time, ‘What God has made clean, you must not call impure.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":10,"text":"“Now this happened three times, and everything was drawn up again into heaven.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":11,"text":"At that very moment, three men who had been sent to me from Caesarea arrived at the house where we were.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":12,"text":"The Spirit told me to accompany them with no doubts at all. These six brothers also accompanied me, and we went into the man’s house.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":13,"text":"He reported to us how he had seen the angel standing in his house and saying, ‘Send to Joppa, and call for Simon, who is also named Peter.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":14,"text":"He will speak a message to you by which you and all your household will be saved.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":15,"text":"“As I began to speak, the Holy Spirit came down on them, just as on us at the beginning.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":16,"text":"I remembered the word of the Lord, how he said, ‘John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":17,"text":"If, then, God gave them the same gift that he also gave to us when we believed in the Lord Jesus Christ, how could I possibly hinder God?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":18,"text":"When they heard this they became silent. And they glorified God, saying, “So then, God has given repentance resulting in life even to the Gentiles.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":19,"text":"Now those who had been scattered as a result of the persecution that started because of Stephen made their way as far as Phoenicia, Cyprus, and Antioch, speaking the word to no one except Jews.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":20,"text":"But there were some of them, men from Cyprus and Cyrene, who came to Antioch and began speaking to the Greeks also, proclaiming the good news about the Lord Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":21,"text":"The Lord’s hand was with them, and a large number who believed turned to the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":22,"text":"News about them reached the church in Jerusalem, and they sent out Barnabas to travel as far as Antioch.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":23,"text":"When he arrived and saw the grace of God, he was glad and encouraged all of them to remain true to the Lord with devoted hearts,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":24,"text":"for he was a good man, full of the Holy Spirit and of faith. And large numbers of people were added to the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":25,"text":"Then he went to Tarsus to search for Saul,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":26,"text":"and when he found him he brought him to Antioch. For a whole year they met with the church and taught large numbers. The disciples were first called Christians at Antioch.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":27,"text":"In those days some prophets came down from Jerusalem to Antioch.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":28,"text":"One of them, named Agabus, stood up and predicted by the Spirit that there would be a severe famine throughout the Roman world. This took place during the reign of Claudius.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":29,"text":"Each of the disciples, according to his ability, determined to send relief to the brothers and sisters who lived in Judea.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","bookOrder":43,"chapter":11,"verse":30,"text":"They did this, sending it to the elders by means of Barnabas and Saul.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Act","chapter":11,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,8,10,15,18,19,25,27],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Gentile Salvation Defended"},{"beforeVerse":19,"text":"The Church in Antioch"},{"beforeVerse":27,"text":"Famine Relief"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The apostles and the brothers and sisters who were throughout Judea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Act:11:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When Peter went up to Jerusalem, the circumcision party criticized him, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 10:45","book":"Act","chapter":10,"verse":45,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 4:11","book":"Col","chapter":4,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 1:10","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":10,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 10:45","book":"Act","chapter":10,"verse":45},{"label":"Col 4:11","book":"Col","chapter":4,"verse":11},{"label":"1Tm 1:10","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":10}],"footnotes":